Authentication And Authorization

Authentication: Process using which we can uniquely identify users on our application.
This process tells us about who the user is.
The general signup/login/logout flow is used to authenticate a user

Authorization: More about Roles
Process using which we can identify the capabilities of a user i.e. what a user can do on our application

 
 * How to do authentication
 Anything through which we can directly identify unique user
1. Mobile Number
2. Omniauth: Gmail, FB, Github
3. Token Based


* JWT => JSON Web Token

To generate the JWT token, we actually use the client credentials

Using this token, we can even retrieve the info back

Never be using password for generating the JWT token

The JWT token is never stored in the server

It is expired after some time
